LOCUS       thrombin_site              6 aa                     UNK 01-JAN-1980
DEFINITION  Engineered 6-residue thrombin recognition/cleavage site (LVPRGS)
            used to proteolytically remove affinity/solubility tags from
            recombinant fusion proteins; thrombin cleaves after the Arg (LVPR |
            GS), leaving a Gly-Ser N-terminal scar..
